 Ms. Abiola, daughter of late billionaire businessman and winner of the annulled 1993 presidential election, M.K.O. Abiola, has expressed the desire to vie for the position of the National Youth Leader of the All Progressives Congress. The young politician, media entrepreneur and philanthropist declared her intention via a social media post. According to her, the decision to vie for the position followed months of wide consultations with key stakeholders in the party. Party members across the country have been indicating interest in various positions since the APC released its zoning formula for executive offices in its coming national convention. Abiola is known for her philanthropic activities through the Derinsola Abiola Foundation. She also engages in sustained advocacy for women and youth mainstreaming in politics. A Special Assistant to the Speaker of the House of Representatives in the Eighth Assembly, the young Abiola runs a media and political consultancy firm. She has been committed to promoting youth and womenâ€™s interests through politics and the civil society. If elected as youth leader, she stated that she would prioritize the delivery of the youth vote for the APC and give required support to young candidates. She also promised to push for better representation of young people in appointive positions while also safeguarding the interests of Nigerian youths in policy formulation at different levels of government. If elected, she would be the first female youth leader of a political party in Nigeria. 